  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the first interesting research direction regards incorporating advanced NLP technologies, particularly the rapidly evolving Large Language Models (LLMs) (Min et al. 2023).",
    "LLMs represent the state of the art for many NLP tasks and demonstrated remarkable proficiency in classifying and extracting information from documents (Dunn et al. 2022; Xu et al. 2023).",
    "However, integrating these models presents several challenges (Ji et al. 2023).",
    "Firstly, LLMs are trained on general data, resulting in less effective performance in specialised fields and languages with fewer resources.",
    "Secondly, LLMs may generate inaccurate or fabricated information, known as \"hallucinations\"."
  ],
